This picture puzzle from Duke Frederick III of Gottorf's #Kunstkammer‚Äîwhat we might call a "cabinet of curiosities"‚Äîshows Queen Sophie Amalie of Denmark surrounded by eight royal ancestors. ‚Å£‚Å£

‚Å£‚Å£‚Å£‚Å£
So, what's the trick? Each of the refractions made by the faceted lens captures a small fragment of every portrait surrounding Queen Sophie. The shards are reassembled for the viewer's eye into Christian V's likeness. üëÅÔ∏è ‚Å£

"Today's announcement, that the Metropolitan Museum is taking steps to emphasize fashion as an art, is a history-making move in the life of American fashion.
